    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform nurse education funding, cancel debt & reinstate bursaries",
        "additional_details": "Newly qualified nurses in England often graduate with over \u00a360,000 of debt. Research by the the Royal College of Nursing (RCN) and London Economics suggests that forgiving nurse student debt could retain nurses 7\u201310 years longer and save the NHS over \u00a31bn. We believe that the current funding model dissuades people from entering nursing and worsens staff shortages.",
        "background": "Abolish tuition fees for nurse training, reinstate the NHS nursing bursary, and forgive existing student loan debt for nurses working in the NHS.",
